Description: Our purpose has always been to provide a better experience to those who have been ordered to have an interlock device in their vehicle.
Full Description: Arizona Interlock 3104 E Camelback Road #2139 Phoenix, AZ 85016 Phone: (602) 688-2907 Website: http://arizonainterlock.com/ We offer the best service for interlock ignition installation services all over the Phoenix Valley in cities such as Mesa, Chandler, Gilbert, Phoenix, Scottsdale, and more! We don't use outside contractors, so all of our work is done in house so you know you're getting the best service directly from us! Call us today to learn more about how we can help you! Arizona Interlock was founded almost 8 years ago. Our purpose in existing as a company has always been to provide a better experience to those who have been ordered to have the interlock device placed in their vehicle. We have seen our competitor’s dream up hidden fees and surcharges, fail to innovate or improve their product, and overall not providing a level of customer service that you as a paying client would expect from your provider. We have always been at the forefront of innovation in the interlock industry. We are the sole providers of the cup, which disguises your interlock device as a beverage, so as to reduce any uncomfortable moments in public when you need to blow into your device to start your car. We also are the only interlock company that offers a flashcube for your dashboard. This light is a visual cue to the driver that they may need to blow into their device. This is perfect for people who like to play music, drive with the windows open, are hearing impaired, have children or other distractions, now the reminder is not just a beep, but a light blinking on your dashboard, so you do not mess up and get in trouble with the courts for failing to blow. Arizona’s laws concerning DUI and the requirement of an interlock device are some of the toughest in the nation. In addition to jail time and heavy fines, person’s convicted of driving under the influence can expect to be ordered by the courts to have an interlock device placed in their car. These devices measure the alcohol levels in the drivers body by having the driver blow into a tube. Description: New York Triathlon Club is a New York state triathlon club for beginners to experienced people.
Full Description: New York Triathlon (NYTRI) started as a grassroots race production company out of Syracuse, NY in 1983 and is now the longest running triathlon organization in the Northeast. During this period NYTRI worked hard to produce the best value in multi-sport events available to athletes in the Tri-State area. To date, NYTRI has organized over 600 events that drew approximately 100,000 competitors, many of them first-timers to multi-sport competition. Company founder Daniel Honig has been competing in and organizing triathlon events for over four decades. Honig combines his experience as an athlete who personally competed in 150 triathlons, and as a race director for delivering a unique race experience for all levels of expertise. No other organization in the country has produced a more extensive and varied list of events. NYTRI’s organizational expertise and safety record are known and respected nationwide. NYTRI is a not-for-profit, 501(c)(3) organization dedicated to developing the sport of triathlon, duathlon and related multi-sport events for racing, physical fitness, and recreation. Membership includes novice to seasoned athletes from throughout the Tri-state (New York, New Jersey, Connecticut) area. Emphasis is placed on amateur competition. Established in 1983 as the Big Apple Triathlon Club, competitors in NYTRI events receive the highest quality of organization and safety standards.
